lines along the lines that are already given to us by the graph paper. And the

00:00:32.143 --> 00:00:35.884
intersect to help us form the right triangle. Then, we just need to figure out

00:00:35.896 --> 00:00:39.924
the length of each of these legs for each of these triangles. Let's look at leg

00:00:39.936 --> 00:00:44.623
AB as an example for how to deal with the other three triangles on here. We need

00:00:44.635 --> 00:00:49.074
to find out the length of either of the two shorter legs in order to find out

00:00:49.086 --> 00:00:53.343
the hypotenuse. So, we could just count one, two, three, four, five, six, seven.

